    ],
    "identity_□": "Jesus acts from an 'hour' not driven by human demand; he manifests glory through signs, claims the temple as his Father's house, speaks of his body as the true temple, and knows what is in people.",
    "enactment_◇": "At Cana Jesus commands, and water becomes wine; in Jerusalem he goes up, interrupts temple commerce, drives out sellers, and answers authority-challenges with a riddle about the temple raised in three days.",
    "effect_Δ": "Disciples believe as glory is revealed; conflict over authority intensifies; the temple saying is understood after resurrection; many believe because of signs, yet Jesus does not entrust himself due to heart-knowledge."
  },
